{"TopicId":217670,"ForumId":198,"TopicTitle":"KSP2 Should be Looking for Save/Craft File Thumbnails in Their Current Location, Instead KSP2 is Looking for their Created Location.","CreatedByName":"Anth","CreatedById":161238,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-12T02:28:17Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Anth","CreatedById":161238,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-12T02:28:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.1.2 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Windows 10 | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Intel i9 9900 | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0nvidia 3070ti | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E32GB\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIssue:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nIf save files (and meta and png) are moved to another computer, the thumbnail won\u0027t be displayed because the path is most likely different. Also, the Campaign name could also be different.\u003Cbr\u003E\nIf craft files (and meta and png) are moved to a different campaign folder KSP2 will look to the original campaign location instead of the current location.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003ESave File looking to the complete path to the thumbnail including the Campaign folder:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022SaveFileNotePad.png.59a3bc94624035e2dd834f04ae0bcdc9.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002237.50\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/uploads/monthly_2023_06/SaveFileNotePad.png.59a3bc94624035e2dd834f04ae0bcdc9.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003ECraft File looking to the path within the Intercept Games appdata folder including the Campaign folder:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022CraftFileNotePad.png.73212b5be9b16e09807564bed40e3b92.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002237.50\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/uploads/monthly_2023_06/CraftFileNotePad.png.73212b5be9b16e09807564bed40e3b92.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EWhat the end result is for a craft file:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022MissingThumbnail.png.744948981db033b09b2f7b2a7dfbddb7.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/uploads/monthly_2023_06/MissingThumbnail.png.744948981db033b09b2f7b2a7dfbddb7.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGeneric Thumbnails for Save Files Instead of the correct ones:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022m2y2nGC.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/m2y2nGC.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003EConclusion:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nIn my opinion KSP2 just needs to look to the same folder that the save/craft file is located. No need for a path to it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-06-12T02:57:19Z\u0022 title=\u002206/12/2023 02:57  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EJune 12, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Anth12\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}